
##############To Set up Go for Build or run Go Packages 

https://golang.org/dl/

wget https://storage.googleapis.com/golang/go1.5.1.linux-amd64.tar.gz

mkdir ~/software

tar -C ~/software/ -xzf go1.5.1.linux-amd64.tar.gz

export GOPATH=~/.go
export GOROOT=~/software/go
export PATH=$PATH:$GOROOT/bin:$GOPATH/bin

############# To Build package 

go to package path 

rake clean

rake trusty


########### To Run go packages 




firt make path for your work environment ( yourworkPath/go/src/github.com/megamsys/) then paste here your project ex. megamd,gulp or libgo, etc.,

export GOPATH=$GOPATH:/home/USER/code/megam/workspace/go

source ~/.bashrc


then go to your project path
for example:

cd /home/megam/code/workspace/go/src/github.com/megamsys/megamd/



Install the dependencies mercurial and bzr

	   sudo apt-get install mercurial meld

	   sudo apt-get install bzr
           
           sudo apt-get -f install

 make   (only at first time bcz it download dependcies every time so to avoid it  next time use make test)

 make test
NOTE: if you got any error while make or make test remove ~/.go then do make




